<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 3:27PM MDT  by NWS El Paso</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Otero County
through 400 PM MDT...
At 327 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Timberon. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
The Otero Mesa.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
